<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

<section xml:id="Learning-Outcomes" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Learning Outcomes</title>
    <introduction>
        <p> By the end of this course, you should be able to:
      </p>
    </introduction>

    <subsection xml:id="module-1">
      <title>Module 1: Linear Algebra Foundations</title>

      <dl>
        <li>
          <title>Matrix Operations</title>
          <p>
            Perform addition and scalar multiplication; compute matrix
            multiplication and verify dimensions; apply associative and
            distributive properties.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <title>Systems of Linear Equations</title>
          <p>
            Represent systems as augmented matrices; solve systems using
            Gaussian elimination; classify solutions as unique, infinite,
            or none.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <title>Determinants and Inverses</title>
          <p>
            Calculate determinants using cofactor expansion and row
            reduction; compute matrix inverses via row reduction; verify
            inverses by multiplication.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <title>Rank and Linear Independence</title>
          <p>
            Determine matrix rank using reduced row-echelon form; test
            linear independence of vectors; interpret rank in terms of
            solution existence.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <title>Eigenvalues and Eigenvectors</title>
          <p>
            Formulate the characteristic polynomial; compute eigenvalues
            and eigenvectors; normalize and interpret eigenvectors.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <title>Diagonalization and Applications</title>
          <p>
            Check diagonalizability; perform diagonalization using an
            eigenbasis; apply diagonalization to simplify ODE systems.
          </p>
        </li>
      </dl>
    </subsection>

    <subsection xml:id="module-2">
      <title>Module 2: Multivariable Calculus</title>

      <dl>
        <li>
          <title>Partial Derivatives</title>
          <p>
            Compute first and second-order partial derivatives; locate and
            classify critical points using the second derivative test.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <title>Multiple Integrals</title>
          <p>
            Set up double integrals over rectangular and non-rectangular
            regions; change the order of integration; apply change of
            variables; compute volume using triple integrals.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <title>Vector Calculus</title>
          <p>
            Compute gradients of scalar fields; calculate divergence and
            curl of vector fields and interpret their physical meaning.
          </p>
        </li>
      </dl>
    </subsection>

    <subsection xml:id="module-3">
      <title>Module 3: Ordinary Differential Equations (ODE)</title>

      <dl>
        <li>
          <title>First-Order ODEs</title>
          <p>
            Identify separable, linear, exact, and Bernoulli equations;
            apply the appropriate solution method; verify solutions by
            substitution.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <title>Second-Order Linear ODEs</title>
          <p>
            Form characteristic equations; solve for real, repeated, or
            complex roots; construct general solutions and apply initial
            conditions.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <title>Non-Homogeneous ODEs</title>
          <p>
            Identify forcing functions; apply the method of undetermined
            coefficients; use variation of parameters.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <title>Systems of ODEs</title>
          <p>
            Express systems in matrix form; compute eigenvalues and
            eigenvectors; construct solutions using linear combinations.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <title>Special Types</title>
          <p>
            Solve Cauchy–Euler equations; apply Laplace transforms for
            initial value problems.
          </p>
        </li>
      </dl>
    </subsection>

    <subsection xml:id="module-4">
      <title>Module 4: Partial Differential Equations (PDE)</title>

      <dl>
        <li>
          <title>Classification</title>
          <p>
            Identify order and linearity of PDEs; determine type
            (elliptic, parabolic, hyperbolic); explain physical meaning.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <title>Heat Equation</title>
          <p>
            Apply separation of variables; solve resulting ordinary
            differential equations; incorporate boundary conditions.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <title>Wave Equation</title>
          <p>
            Formulate PDEs with initial conditions; solve via separation
            of variables; interpret solutions physically.
          </p>
        </li>
      </dl>
    </subsection>

    <section xml:id="module-5">
      <title>Module 5: Engineering Applications and Modeling</title>

      <dl>
        <li>
          <title>Model Formulation</title>
          <p>
            Identify physical parameters and assumptions; translate
            engineering problems into mathematical models; validate
            models against constraints.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <title>Analytical and Numerical Solutions</title>
          <p>
            Select appropriate analytical or numerical methods; implement
            numerical schemes such as Euler and Runge–Kutta; compare
            results.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <title>Computational Tools</title>
          <p>
            Implement models in MATLAB or Python; visualize results; interpret
            outputs in an engineering context.
          </p>
        </li>
      </dl>
      </subsection>

</section>
